{
  "stem": "14613.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was a capitalist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was a socialist.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But he talked to me, and to my family, like a human being.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I would do anything for him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he did-- when the Germans came in and the war started, he did do a lot of things.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But this, again, is maybe the characteristic of my father, that he was an extremely unusual and good person.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So that he, or even the Germans that worked in our factory-- since they were always good with machinery, there were a lot of Germans working in our factory, they would say to my father, [NON-ENGLISH], that you are a different Jew.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they would do things for my father that normally they could not do-- they were not-- they should not have done.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Once, when they threw us out from our apartment house, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] they took everything.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I mean, they just closed the apartment and we were out.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was one painting of my mother, which I believe my father made for her for their 10th anniversary, which she loved very much.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "All she wanted was to get this painting back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And some of these-- two or three of these Germans that worked in my father's factory-- and of course, they became big shots in Gestapo, and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "When my father talked to them, they said, we will go to the German who took over the apartment, and we will talk to him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they did go, and asked them for the painting.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But of course, I remember what the German answered.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And he said, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Which means, I would better burn it than to give it to the Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
